{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_48","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' ralph-burning-rewrite/20260311184405-impl-notes.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- **Three payload families cover all 16 stages.** Rather than 16 individual payload types, stages are grouped into Planning (4 stages), Execution (5 stages), and Validation (7 stages) families. Each family shares a typed payload struct. This matches the spec's grouping of required fields by family and avoids type explosion while still enforcing all required fields per category.\n- **Schema validation via serde deserialization.** JSON Schema generation uses `schemars` (0.8) for external consumers and documentation. Actual schema validation is implemented via `serde_json::from_value` deserialization, which enforces the same structural requirements as the generated schema. This avoids an additional `jsonschema` validator dependency while satisfying the \"JSON Schema generation/validation\" requirement.\n- **Contract evaluation returns `Result<EvalSuccess, ContractError>`.** `EvalSuccess` carries both the `ValidatedBundle` (payload + artifact) and an optional `outcome_failure` field. This models the distinction between hard failures (schema/domain/render — no bundle returned) and workflow-level outcome failures (QA/review non-passing — bundle IS returned, but with `QaReviewOutcomeFailure` flag).\n- **`ReviewOutcome::is_passing()` treats only `Approved` as passing.** `ConditionallyApproved`, `RequestChanges`, and `Rejected` all map to `QaReviewOutcomeFailure` per the spec's \"not cleanly approved\" language.\n- **Semantic validation rules are intentionally minimal.** Planning requires non-empty problem_framing, at least one work item with positive order. Execution requires non-empty change_summary, at least one step with positive order. Validation requires follow_up_or_amendments when outcome is non-passing. These enforce the spec's required-field contracts without over-constraining domain logic that belongs to later slices.\n- **`ContractError` placed in `shared/error.rs`** alongside `AppError`, with a `failure_class()` method mapping each variant to its `FailureClass`. Render errors map to `DomainValidationFailure` since they indicate an internal contract consistency issue rather than a distinct failure class.\n- **`StageId::ALL` and `StageId::display_name()` added** to support registry completeness verification and human-readable Markdown headings respectively. No existing enum variants or flow orderings were modified.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- **JSON Schema validation is via serde, not a dedicated JSON Schema validator.** The spec says \"JSON Schema generation/validation.\" We generate schemas via `schemars` and validate structurally via serde deserialization. A dedicated `jsonschema` crate was considered but adds complexity for equivalent validation coverage. The generated schemas are available via `StageContract::json_schema()` for any consumer that needs standalone schema validation.\n- **No separate `RenderFailure` in `FailureClass` enum.** The spec's failure-class enum has six members and doesn't include a render-specific class. Render errors (which should not occur if schema+semantic pass) are mapped to `DomainValidationFailure` in `ContractError::failure_class()`.\n\n## Testing\n- **48 unit tests pass** (up from 12 in loop 1), covering:\n  - Registry completeness: every `StageId` and every stage in every built-in flow resolves to a contract\n  - Family mapping correctness: planning/execution/validation stages map to their expected families\n  - Schema failure short-circuits: invalid JSON produces `SchemaValidation` error, never reaches semantic validation or rendering\n  - Domain failure short-circuits: schema-valid but semantically invalid payloads produce `DomainValidation` error, never reach rendering\n  - Successful evaluation: each family produces a `ValidatedBundle` with non-empty artifact\n  - QA/review outcome failure: non-passing outcomes return bundle WITH `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`, not schema/domain errors\n  - JSON Schema generation: every stage produces a non-trivial schema\n  - Deterministic rendering: same payload rendered twice produces byte-identical output\n  - Artifact structure: section headings, content markers, display names all verified\n  - Conformance scenario IDs (SC-EVAL-001 through SC-EVAL-007): explicit tests mapping to Gherkin scenarios\n- **`cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` passes clean**\n- **9 Gherkin conformance scenario IDs** added in `tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature` (SC-EVAL-001 through SC-EVAL-009)\n- To verify: `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` from the `ralph-burning-rewrite/` directory\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: APPROVED\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Checklist\n- [x] Contract coverage is complete for all built-in presets, with no flow ID or stage-order changes ([mod.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs#L23), [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L65), [flow_preset_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_preset_test.rs#L23)).\n- [x] Typed payload models and generated schemas cover all 16 supported stages via the planning/execution/validation contract families ([payloads.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs#L16), [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L101)).\n- [x] Family requirements are enforced: planning/execution payload structure is validated semantically, and validation stages require follow-up data when outcomes are not cleanly approved ([contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L170), [payloads.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs#L82)).\n- [x] Evaluation order is fixed and short-circuiting: schema validation runs first, semantic validation second, non-passing review outcomes error before rendering, and callers get either a full bundle or an error ([contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L110), [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L135), [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L245)).\n- [x] Required failure classes are present, and non-passing QA/review/completion outcomes map to `qa_review_outcome_failure` rather than schema/domain failure ([domain.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs#L11), [error.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs#L41)).\n- [x] Renderers are deterministic, stage-aware through `StageId`, and derive artifacts from structured payload fields only ([renderers.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs#L15), [renderer_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/renderer_test.rs#L61), [renderer_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/renderer_test.rs#L206)).\n- [x] Unit/conformance coverage exists for registry completeness, schema failure, domain failure, QA/review outcome failure, schema-alignment checks, and deterministic rendering ([stage_contract_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs#L66), [stage_contract_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs#L318), [stage_contracts.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature#L8)).\n\n## Notes\nThe prior mismatch on non-passing review semantics is fixed: `evaluate()` now returns `Err(ContractError::QaReviewOutcome { .. })` before rendering, with matching unit and Gherkin expectations ([contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L117), [error.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs#L51), [stage_contract_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs#L271), [stage_contracts.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature#L53)). Verification passed via `nix develop -c cargo test` and `nix develop -c cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`; the test run reported 51 unit tests and 5 CLI tests passing.\n\n---"}}
